What exactly is Arrays.asList()?
It is a shortcut to quickly make a list.
Instead of:
List<String> list = new ArrayList<>();

list.add("eat");
list.add("tea");
list.add("ate");
you can simply write:
List<String> list = Arrays.asList("eat", "tea", "ate");

Arrays.asList() creates a fixed-size List backed by an array.
We can modify elements using set(), but we cannot add or remove elements.
If we need a truly dynamic list, we wrap it inside new ArrayList<>(...).
